1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,390 --> 00:01:42,270
[I Don't Want To Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:44,750
[Jinhai Third People's Hospital]

4
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,680
It's okay. Have a good rest.

5
00:01:48,780 --> 00:01:49,700
Be careful of what you eat.

6
00:01:50,009 --> 00:01:51,020
Thank you!

7
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,080
Li Jin Bu.

8
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:59,670
You better study medicine
when you grow up

9
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,040
and become a doctor.

10
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,310
No.

11
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,190
Why not?

12
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,350
If you become a doctor,

13
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,030
you can treat me at home

14
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:11,720
if I'm sick.

15
00:02:12,230 --> 00:02:13,630
We can save a lot of money.

16
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,880
You think treating guests is expensive,

17
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:17,270
so you want me to become a cook.

18
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,320
When you cry because of a drama,

19
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,000
you want me to be an actress.

20
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,400
When you are moved by a concert,

21
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,780
you want me to learn singing.

22
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:25,160
Now that you are sick,

23
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,480
you want me to be a doctor.

24
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:27,880
What if one day you
can't afford flight tickets,

25
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,800
will you want me to learn
how to fly a plane?

26
00:02:30,390 --> 00:02:32,150
That sounds like a good idea.

27
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,640
Becoming a pilot is quite good too.

28
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,720
But I'm afraid that you're
not capable of learning it.

29
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,040
Well, Li Jin Bu.

30
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,579
Didn't you peel an orange for me?

31
00:02:40,579 --> 00:02:41,680
Why are you eating it alone?

32
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,120
Come on, give me some.

33
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,350
You'd better learn how to peel oranges.

34
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,310
Li Jin Bu.

35
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,040
[Episode 10: One Quater Ideals,
Three Quarters Bad Luck]

36
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:48,480
I...

37
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,510
Just let me have a bite.

38
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:52,270
I am a patient.

39
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,710
You guys are truly amazing.

40
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,040
You can even start a fight
because of a tug-of-war.

41
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,310
Do you really have too much

42
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,360
pent-up energy?

43
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:13,600
Ms. Yang, I think there is
a slight misunderstanding.

44
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:14,360
In a competitive race,

45
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,030
tiny frictions are inevitable.

46
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,440
That was just a slight chaos.

47
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,790
Mr Wu.

48
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,870
This is a serious situation.

49
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,520
How can you make excuses for them?

50
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,510
If you don't discipline them,

51
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:25,730
the situation will get worse.

52
00:03:25,730 --> 00:03:26,420
You're right.

53
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,520
Wu Zhi Xun.

54
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,040
You...

55
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,190
Why are you here too?

56
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,880
Are you now joining them?

57
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,600
Just you wait.

58
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,020
After the sports meeting,

59
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:45,000
I will discipline you myself.

60
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,360
You drove Ms Yang so mad.

61
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,440
And you.

62
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,680
You should also think about your problem.

63
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:51,670
Okay.

64
00:03:56,579 --> 00:03:57,660
You...
I...

65
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:02,910
Are you alright?

66
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:05,870
We're alright.

67
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,190
Wash your face

68
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,160
and dress those wound.

69
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:12,270
You make my blood pressure rise.

70
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:17,310
You...

71
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:17,750
You...

72
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:33,390
Are you alright?

73
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,000
I'm fine.

74
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,640
Band-aid.

75
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,400
I don't need it.

76
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,720
Why not? Your face...

77
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,190
It's grazed.

78
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:49,720
Chen Jun He.

79
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:50,740
Sorry.

80
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,230
[The Olympic athletes]

81
00:05:10,230 --> 00:05:12,230
deeply inspires us.

82
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:15,310
We also need to show
the spirit of Olympic athletes

83
00:05:15,310 --> 00:05:17,510
and strive for the first place
in the arena

84
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:20,520
[and scale new heights in our study.]

85
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,960
[A note by Qin Xiao Xiao
of First Year, Class No. 3.]

86
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,720
Look at Lin Xue Wei.

87
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,160
She's good at reading scripts.

88
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,480
Look at you.

89
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,840
You were fouled out of throwing a discus.

90
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,080
It's not my fault.

91
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,360
There were two lines.

92
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,920
I didn't know I stood on the wrong side.

93
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,630
No one told me.

94
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:41,880
Not only did you get your direction wrong,

95
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,080
but your discus almost hit the principal.

96
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,400
That's most terrible.

97
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,550
You also broke a hurdle.

98
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:48,750
Aren't you terrible too?

99
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:51,070
Did I do it on purpose?

100
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,280
I am not too bad.

101
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,110
I got third place for the pole vault.

102
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,200
There were only three people competing.

103
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,440
You lost your relay baton.

104
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,680
How dare you rebuke me?

105
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:07,600
The whole team failed.

106
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,670
Incredible.

107
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,560
Now, I am the one
who can turn this around.

108
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,070
I am going now.

109
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,430
The worst of all sets out.

110
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:30,840
Dude,

111
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,990
I have asked around several times.

112
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:33,560
That girl is running in this round.

113
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,080
Do you see the girl wearing

114
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,800
a yellow hat there?

115
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,400
She is responsible for
writing down rankings

116
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,670
on her clipboard.

117
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:41,540
I have asked.

118
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:42,720
She only writes down the numbers,

119
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,630
not names.

120
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,159
Lao Da,

121
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,560
you try to divert her attention.

122
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,270
Xiao Huo,

123
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,640
you change the number.

124
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,920
Don't be caught.

125
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,680
Can it work?

126
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:52,720
You will never know if you don't try.

127
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:53,360
Maybe it will work.

128
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:54,720
With that sincere intention,

129
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,040
it will definitely work.

130
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,040
That's right.

131
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,040
But she doesn't know we are helping her.

132
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,080
Why are you talking so much?

133
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,690
Are my words falling on deaf ear?

134
00:07:02,690 --> 00:07:03,660
Of course not.

135
00:07:03,670 --> 00:07:04,430
I'm going.

136
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:25,760
0-3-2-5.

137
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:26,320
Did you memorise it?

138
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:27,840
I have it imprinted in my heart.

139
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:28,480
Go.

140
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,320
Oh my gosh!

141
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,720
You must apologise to me.

142
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,280
Why are you on the ground?

143
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,210
You knocked me over.

144
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,680
It was you who knocked me over.

145
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:43,560
You're ridiculous.

146
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,080
You must apologise to me.

147
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,470
You bumped into me while running.

148
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:49,110
I was going to let it slide.

149
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:50,720
Hi there.

150
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,750
Give me the long-distance running ranking.

151
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:52,840
The teacher needs it now.

152
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,070
He knocked me over

153
00:07:54,070 --> 00:07:55,320
but didn't want to let me go.

154
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:56,920
I will give the ranking to the teacher.

155
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,380
You two sort this out.

156
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:00,230
Who are you?

157
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:00,840
You can't go.

158
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,190
You must give me an apology.

159
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:06,510
0-3-2-5.

160
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:14,310
Mr Huang, what's the matter?

161
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,720
Look.

162
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:17,800
The number of the first place was erased,

163
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,120
and replaced by 0-3-2-5.

164
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,030
Now, 0-3-2-5 is in first place,

165
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:22,280
and also fourth place.

166
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,550
Aren't you 0-3-2-5?

167
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:24,400
What happened?

168
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,400
Are there two of you?

169
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,310
Do you have magic powers?

170
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,120
What's this? Mr Huang.

171
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,720
It has nothing to do with me.

172
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,039
Are you denying it?

173
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,960
You can't run, so you falsify the result?

174
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:35,940
What's the use of falsifying?

175
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,070
Everyone witnessed the race.

176
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:39,200
But I didn't falsify it.

177
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,120
How do you explain this?

178
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:43,419
Fine.

179
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:44,910
You're not admitting, right?

180
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,240
I'm going to talk to Mr Wu.

181
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,680
Mr. Huang, I...

182
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,280
I really didn't falsify it.

183
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,020
Can't anyone of you

184
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,640
give me a peace of mind?

185
00:08:58,210 --> 00:09:00,070
I might end up writing
the reflective report today.

186
00:09:00,070 --> 00:09:02,320
Mr Wu, I am really wronged.

187
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,240
Don't move.

188
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,990
Put down your hands.

189
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:11,360
Stand still.

190
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,640
Mr Wu.

191
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:18,600
Get a good look at these two.

192
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,870
One put up an act.

193
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:20,990
The other falsified the result.

194
00:09:20,990 --> 00:09:22,400
What a great team you make!

195
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:24,200
You two did that?

196
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:25,680
It was not Li Qing Tong?

197
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,080
You can go.

198
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,560
It was Li Qing Tong from your class

199
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,640
who got two senior to assist her.

200
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,310
You are quite capable.

201
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,600
No, I didn't.

202
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,150
I don't know them.

203
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,240
Shut up.

204
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:38,960
Stand still.

205
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,760
When both your homeroom teachers are here,

206
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:42,990
I will deal with all three of you.

207
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:47,640
Ms Yang, I think this must be
a misunderstanding.

208
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,480
You two tell Chen Jun He

209
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:53,550
I will get back at him.

210
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,280
No, wait.

211
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,120
It's an accident. Really.

212
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,560
We intended to help you.

213
00:09:57,220 --> 00:09:58,120
Help me?

214
00:09:58,280 --> 00:09:59,050
You want to help me?

215
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,120
Is this helping me?

216
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,400
Ms Yang, please calm down.

217
00:10:01,590 --> 00:10:03,430
Let's investigate it first.

218
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:05,080
What if it turns out differently?

219
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:05,920
She is just a girl...

220
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:06,630
Attention everyone.

221
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:07,360
Ms Yang...

222
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,640
Announcement.

223
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,230
Announcement.

224
00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:14,110
We don't have to do this.

225
00:10:14,110 --> 00:10:17,750
Niu Xiao Huo and Liu Da Da
of Senior Year, Class No. 1.

226
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:20,000
Li Qing Tong of Second Year, Class No. 3.

227
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,680
The three falsified the race result.

228
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,440
This is an announcement
to condemn their action

229
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:26,200
Their action will be dealt with
after the race.

230
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,990
Hope everyone takes this as a warning,

231
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:29,720
and maintain dignity in the games.

232
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,510
What's going on?

233
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,400
Li Qing Tong.

234
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:41,000
Go away.

235
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,320
Li Qing Tong.

236
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,940
Didn't you say we had settled our scores?

237
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,920
Why are you still not letting me go?

238
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,270
I really wanted to help you.

239
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,600
I didn't know it would turn out this way.

240
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,270
Thank you for this mess.

241
00:10:59,570 --> 00:11:00,580
-Dude
-Dude.

242
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,300
I have to go.

243
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:03,530
Me too.

244
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,710
Dude, we didn't mean it.

245
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,120
You only told me to change
the number for first place,

246
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,470
you didn't tell me to change
the other one.

247
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:10,840
I'm going to change your brain now.

248
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,520
Dude, calm down.

249
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:30,890
[Reflective Report]

250
00:11:31,470 --> 00:11:32,790
Have you ever done
a written self-criticism?

251
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:35,840
Oh my goodness!

252
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,440
You never written one before.

253
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,800
Your life is incomplete.

254
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,240
Have you ever played truant?

255
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,100
No.

256
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,200
Don't tell me that you've
never been late for school.

257
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:46,200
No.

258
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:47,920
Then have you ever got
second place in the exam?

259
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,270
Just once.

260
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,960
We are all human beings.

261
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:58,080
But our gap is too wide.

262
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,840
We are just rubbish.

263
00:12:10,340 --> 00:12:11,950
Why are you crying?

264
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,790
The more I think about it,
the madder I get.

265
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,080
I was treated unfairly.

266
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,670
I did nothing wrong.

267
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:22,390
Why was I condemned via announcement?

268
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,440
I can't accept it.

269
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,270
In that case,

270
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,520
after Ms Yang comes back,

271
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,400
let's clarify the whole thing.

272
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,040
Forget it.

273
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,520
It will only get more messy.

274
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,480
Why are you chatting?

275
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:37,120
Why are you here?

276
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,230
You also want to write a report?

277
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,110
Where is my paper?

278
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,200
Here.

279
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,300
Here.

280
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:44,940
Yes.

281
00:12:45,310 --> 00:12:46,000
Bye, Ms Yang.

282
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,350
How's the bruise on your face?

283
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,080
It doesn't hurt anymore.

284
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,520
I didn't reach top three in race.

285
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,640
Can we still have a barbecue?

286
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,600
No.

287
00:13:24,630 --> 00:13:25,840
[Wang Leehom]

288
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:30,750
For me?

289
00:13:31,070 --> 00:13:33,240
Barbecue is for reaching top three.

290
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,520
This is for not reaching top three.

291
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,960
This is way better than barbecue.

292
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,320
If I knew it earlier,
I would have come in last.

293
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:44,710
If you come in last,

294
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:45,710
you don't even get anything.

295
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,890
Thank you.

296
00:13:58,160 --> 00:13:59,350
That's enough.

297
00:13:59,350 --> 00:14:00,670
You have been looking at it
for the whole night.

298
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,440
It's too precious.

299
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,350
Should I open it?

300
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:09,840
Let me do it for you.

301
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:11,670
Stop.

302
00:14:11,670 --> 00:14:12,600
Nobody can touch this.

303
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:25,230
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

304
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:30,960
Mr Wu.

305
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,310
About yesterday,

306
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,840
do you believe in me?

307
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,400
You must believe that I was wronged.

308
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,840
I was framed.

309
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,080
It doesn't matter if I believe you or not.

310
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,040
People only care about the results.

311
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,280
Why did the two boys

312
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,560
frame you without any reason?

313
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,000
No, wait.

314
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,560
We had a...

315
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,790
A little friction.

316
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,480
They just wanted to
play a trick on me yesterday.

317
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,510
It's no big deal.

318
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:02,360
Yesterday,

319
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:04,710
I was scolded by the principal,
head of department

320
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,840
and then the head of Second Year too.

321
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,550
Do you know

322
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,840
how it feels to be scolded as a teacher?

323
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:12,190
Can you settle your mind,

324
00:15:12,190 --> 00:15:14,200
and pay your attention to your studies?

325
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,240
Go to class now.

326
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,360
Ten metres.

327
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,030
What?

328
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,960
From now on, we must

329
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,230
keep a distance of ten metres.

330
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,200
Never come near me.

331
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,430
Wait, can you listen to my explanation?

332
00:15:43,430 --> 00:15:44,440
Don't move.

333
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,350
What are you doing?

334
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:04,760
Reciprocating.

335
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:16,800
Thank you.

336
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,040
Did you memorise the notes?

337
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,100
I'm trying.

338
00:16:27,260 --> 00:16:28,040
I'm trying.

339
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:31,920
If...

340
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,790
If you really can't memorise them,

341
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:35,280
I can...

342
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,320
Don't worry.

343
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,750
I will keep my promise this time.

344
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,040
If I can't memorise them,

345
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,480
I will not waste any more your time.

346
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,460
Okay.

347
00:16:53,360 --> 00:17:00,500
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

348
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:11,839
Take your exam seriously.

349
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:12,680
Cheating is not allowed.

350
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,230
What are you doing?

351
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:50,830
You are not allowed to hand in
the papers ahead of time.

352
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,340
Check your papers several times.

353
00:18:05,470 --> 00:18:07,040
I have warned you twice.

354
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:07,840
No exam for you!

355
00:18:08,550 --> 00:18:10,880
I didn't see it. My pen fell.

356
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,070
Who are you trying to fool?

357
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,910
Keep your eyes on your own paper.

358
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:04,550
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

359
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:12,700
[Final Examination Ranking
for Second-Year Students]

360
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,120
[First Place: Wu Zhi Xun]

361
00:19:32,410 --> 00:19:36,400
[72nd Place: Li Qing Tong]

362
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:46,180
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

363
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,160
Let's have dinner.

364
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:49,400
Wait.

365
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,440
Before we eat,

366
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,560
I have something to ask you.

367
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:55,480
Are you satisfied with

368
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:56,760
this exam?

369
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:58,230
Dad,

370
00:19:58,520 --> 00:19:59,880
I got first place.

371
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:02,840
It's a must that you get the first place
in an ordinary school.

372
00:20:03,020 --> 00:20:03,830
What I am asking you is,

373
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,600
are you satisfied with your result?

374
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,200
Firstly,

375
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,910
you only beat the second place

376
00:20:09,910 --> 00:20:10,840
by four points.

377
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,750
You didn't get a perfect score
for the math paper.

378
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:15,390
You even had a wrong answer
in the English paper.

379
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,360
As for your essay,

380
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:18,910
it's just well-worn cliche.

381
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:20,080
Didn't you realise

382
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,280
these problems?

383
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:23,040
Do you know the reason?

384
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,120
I will tell you.

385
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,440
Are you giving a girl remedial lessons?

386
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:29,960
No.

387
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:30,590
Zhi Xun,

388
00:20:31,020 --> 00:20:33,280
your father had checked with the school.

389
00:20:34,020 --> 00:20:35,960
We were both members in a study group.

390
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,800
But after this semester,

391
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,800
I didn't give her lessons any more.

392
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:39,920
What do you mean?

393
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:42,230
When you gave her remedial lessons,

394
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,760
your study was not affected.

395
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,840
But now that you don't,
your grades dropped.

396
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:47,870
What are you thinking?

397
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:48,840
Besides,

398
00:20:49,190 --> 00:20:50,640
the bruise in your face

399
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,240
was caused by accident

400
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:53,350
or by fighting

401
00:20:53,350 --> 00:20:54,880
with your schoolmates.

402
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,430
You are clear about that.

403
00:20:56,770 --> 00:20:58,750
Does it have anything to do
with that girl?

404
00:20:58,750 --> 00:20:59,750
No, it doesn't.

405
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:01,560
I got wounded during the sports meeting.

406
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,030
Why did you take part in sports?

407
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:04,150
Are you an athlete?

408
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,040
Don't you know what your top priority is?

409
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:07,320
Since you were young,

410
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:08,840
your mom and I spent

411
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,240
all our financial and material resources

412
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:11,320
to support your study.

413
00:21:11,510 --> 00:21:13,390
Are you worthy of us?

414
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:15,760
What are you doing?

415
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,110
What's with that attitude?

416
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:18,640
I did nothing wrong.

417
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:20,360
I didn't slack off in my study as well.

418
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:21,520
That girl...

419
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,920
She is only my friend.

420
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,000
I hope you can respect my friend.

421
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,960
Enough. Stop talking.

422
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,080
Let's have dinner.

423
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,110
I am not hungry. I'm going to the library.

424
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,680
Look at him.

425
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,800
He doesn't listen any more.

426
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,200
Isn't he rebelling?

427
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:37,880
Wu Zhi Xun.

428
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:38,790
Listen.

429
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:39,760
From now on,

430
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,400
you are not allowed to
go near your classmates,

431
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,550
especially that girl.

432
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:43,510
Enough.

433
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,680
Can you talk reasonably?

434
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,880
Why do you have to get mad?

435
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,030
Let's have dinner.

436
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:52,850
[May Dreams Come True]

437
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,800
Why are you so late?

438
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,910
Something made you unhappy?

439
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:15,870
How do you know that?

440
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:18,480
There is a dark cloud above your head.

441
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:20,830
I can see thunder, lightning, and rain.

442
00:22:26,670 --> 00:22:27,840
What happened to you?

443
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,630
I had a conflict

444
00:22:30,630 --> 00:22:31,710
with my parents.

445
00:22:33,270 --> 00:22:34,680
That's no big deal.

446
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:35,990
I have had conflicts with my mom

447
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,520
for over a decade.

448
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:38,520
It's nothing.

449
00:22:43,110 --> 00:22:44,150
I know.

450
00:22:44,150 --> 00:22:45,640
You must have quarrelled
with your parents.

451
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,860
But I am beaten by my mom every day.

452
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:49,720
It's not something that is

453
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:50,870
worth being angry about.

454
00:22:52,950 --> 00:22:54,320
Let me help you to
drive away the dark cloud.

455
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,240
What are you going to do?

456
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,300
Later,

457
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:00,430
we are going to have a barbecue.

458
00:23:00,990 --> 00:23:02,080
Do you want to join us?

459
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:04,120
I promise that you'll be happy
in 10 minutes.

460
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:04,800
By then,

461
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,150
it will be impossible to not laugh.

462
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:07,080
I won't go.

463
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:08,000
I have to do these questions.

464
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,910
It's only going to take a while.

465
00:23:09,940 --> 00:23:11,800
Just take it as a break.

466
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:12,990
You can go with them.

467
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:16,950
You really won't go?

468
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:17,830
I won't go.

469
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,160
I'm leaving then.

470
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:29,840
You can drop by later if you want.

471
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,110
It's the barbecue restaurant
in front of our school.

472
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,680
We will be there for a long time.

473
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:36,310
If you change your mind,

474
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,920
just drop by any time.

475
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,520
I think the chicken kebabs are delicious.

476
00:24:14,270 --> 00:24:15,000
I think the meat is delicious.

477
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,860
You'd better eat less.

478
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:18,110
You are already chubby.

479
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:21,000
What are you looking at?

480
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:25,560
I invited Wu Zhi Xun to join us.

481
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,320
I think he will come.

482
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,720
What were you thinking?

483
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:31,870
If Wu Zhi Xun

484
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:33,630
joins us for barbeque,

485
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,680
it will be like a deity
descending to earth.

486
00:24:37,150 --> 00:24:38,720
A deity can indeed descend to earth.

487
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,280
However,

488
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,670
it's not so possible

489
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:41,770
for Wu Zhi Xun to come here.

490
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:42,840
What are you talking about?

491
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:44,720
Why is it impossible?

492
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,000
Aren't we all friends?

493
00:24:46,780 --> 00:24:48,240
It's impossible.

494
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,160
Let me ask you.

495
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:54,400
If he really came, what will you do?

496
00:24:55,310 --> 00:24:56,440
If he really came,

497
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:58,120
I will eat the skewer.

498
00:24:58,390 --> 00:24:59,240
He...

499
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:07,880
Why are you here?

500
00:25:08,020 --> 00:25:08,640
I

501
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,710
happen to pass by.

502
00:25:10,900 --> 00:25:11,500
Come.

503
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:17,680
Here you go.

504
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:24,030
Waiter, 20 more kebabs.

505
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:25,200
Okay.

506
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,080
Can you eat spicy food?

507
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:27,600
A little bit.

508
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,560
Fan Shui Shui, give him a soda.

509
00:25:30,190 --> 00:25:31,270
He doesn't drink carbonated beverages.

510
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,270
It's okay.

511
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:33,400
I can drink some.

512
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:42,160
If my mom knows that I am having dinner
with the top of the class,

513
00:25:42,390 --> 00:25:43,150
she will elated.

514
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:53,920
Eat your skewer.

515
00:25:55,150 --> 00:25:55,910
Please, Xiao.

516
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:58,080
Please let me eat some meat.

517
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,040
This too hard.

518
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:00,110
Stop talking.

519
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:01,630
Eat your skewer.

520
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:05,390
Wait. I was just kidding.

521
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,550
I must correct your habit
of boasting today.

522
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:11,040
Go on.

523
00:26:12,020 --> 00:26:12,550
Go on.

524
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:29,200
Be gentle.

525
00:26:30,780 --> 00:26:31,400
You are

526
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,400
getting old.

527
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:35,040
Why did you work recklessly?

528
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:37,630
It's because this is the first time

529
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,520
I work in a construction site.

530
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:44,480
Dad.

531
00:26:45,990 --> 00:26:47,440
My daughter, you are up?

532
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,510
What's the matter with you?

533
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:50,710
It's nothing.

534
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,400
I worked too hard.

535
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,040
What did you do to yourself?

536
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:57,800
It's nothing to do with you.

537
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,480
Why does it have nothing to do with me?

538
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:02,760
You are hurting my dad.

539
00:27:02,760 --> 00:27:03,640
Let me do it.

540
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:05,600
Great!

541
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:07,320
I can have a rest.

542
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:10,600
Here?

543
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:11,410
Yes.

544
00:27:13,710 --> 00:27:15,400
With my daughter's tiny fingers,

545
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:17,520
my pain immediately goes away.

546
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:22,160
Did you let Hua wash the dishes?

547
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:22,760
Where is she?

548
00:27:23,020 --> 00:27:24,960
She is working at Mu Dan Hotel.

549
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,150
Look at that girl.

550
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:27,470
She's much better than you.

551
00:27:28,230 --> 00:27:29,280
It's your turn to wash the dishes tonight.

552
00:27:30,430 --> 00:27:31,310
Look at my mom.

553
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:33,830
She makes me feel like
I am capable of nothing.

554
00:27:33,830 --> 00:27:34,880
But I'm good at massage.

555
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:35,590
Right? Dad?

556
00:27:41,570 --> 00:27:43,410
[Mu Dan Hotel]

557
00:27:43,410 --> 00:27:44,930
[Mu Dan Hotel Bus Schedule]

558
00:28:26,550 --> 00:28:28,040
I knew you must be in the bookstore.

559
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:28,720
Did you just arrive?

560
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:37,480
You are reading this today?

561
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:49,430
I will read Pipi Lu today.

562
00:28:49,430 --> 00:28:50,630
Let's sit here and read today.

563
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:54,880
I won't disturb you.

564
00:29:21,790 --> 00:29:23,200
Do you want to say something?

565
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:25,510
You must be holding it back
for a long time.

566
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:26,680
No, I don't.

567
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,560
I...

568
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:28,440
I won't say a word.

569
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,200
Just go ahead.

570
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:36,310
I think...

571
00:29:36,310 --> 00:29:38,000
I think this part is really well-written.

572
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:41,030
I think that those who write fairytales
are really angels.

573
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:42,440
I like Pipi Lu since I was very young.

574
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:45,040
I think everything about Pipi Lu is real.

575
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,440
Do you know the clock of earth?

576
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:49,200
It's about...

577
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,840
You are not interested to hear it, right?

578
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:54,110
No.

579
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:55,760
Go ahead.

580
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,920
Well, can I read you one paragraph?

581
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:00,160
Definitely.

582
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:05,000
He suddenly finds

583
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:07,240
a big colorful cloud below.

584
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,360
When Pipi Lu loosens his grip,

585
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:09,430
he falls down.

586
00:30:09,430 --> 00:30:11,630
The firecracker shoots
straight into the sun.

587
00:30:11,630 --> 00:30:13,360
Pi Pilu keeps falling.

588
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,910
After a long time,

589
00:30:14,910 --> 00:30:17,080
it feels like he has fallen
into a cotton pile.

590
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:18,670
When he opens his eyes...

591
00:30:59,790 --> 00:31:01,470
[Pipi Lu Collection]

592
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:27,680
Hello!

593
00:31:28,750 --> 00:31:29,830
Are you a high school student?

594
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:31,080
Who are you?

595
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:32,640
I am a teacher.

596
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:34,880
Here's my card.

597
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:35,400
Please have a look.

598
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:38,270
[Tian Jia Ni]

599
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:40,240
Aviation college?

600
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:41,040
Yes.

601
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:42,880
Are you interested in being a stewardess?

602
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:44,840
Stewardess?

603
00:31:45,590 --> 00:31:46,320
Me?

604
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:48,080
How can I become a stewardess?

605
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,280
You are totally perfect.

606
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:50,560
You matched all the criteria.

607
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,720
It will be a pity if you
don't become a stewardess.

608
00:31:52,070 --> 00:31:52,680
Please take a look.

609
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:54,120
If you are interested, please call me.

610
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,280
Be confident about yourself.

611
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,240
Keep your spirits up.

612
00:32:03,170 --> 00:32:05,370
[One-Month Summer Holiday Training]

613
00:32:05,380 --> 00:32:07,580
[Fee only 500 yuan if you pass the cut-off
point for College Entrance Examination]

614
00:32:08,030 --> 00:32:09,640
Aviation college?

615
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:11,280
Is it reliable?

616
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:12,960
How is it not?

617
00:32:13,190 --> 00:32:13,720
Look!

618
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,070
Here are the phone number and address.

619
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:17,400
That Mr Tian

620
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:18,760
looks like a decent man.

621
00:32:18,910 --> 00:32:20,280
You have to pay for training?

622
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:23,870
Five hundred yuan.

623
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,320
It's indeed a little expensive.

624
00:32:27,610 --> 00:32:29,640
[Daily Neccessity Supermarket
and Restaurant]

625
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,480
After paying the fees,

626
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:36,840
we can join the training.

627
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,560
It only takes one month.

628
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:40,200
As long as we pass
the college entrance exam,

629
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,640
we will be directly admitted
into the aviation college.

630
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:43,110
How much does it cost?

631
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:46,870
Five hundred yuan per person.

632
00:32:46,870 --> 00:32:48,190
It's too expensive.

633
00:32:48,630 --> 00:32:49,760
Can you lend me some money?

634
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,240
You have to pay me back.

635
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,400
Is there any requirement for body figure?

636
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:59,320
He didn't tell me
any specific requirements.

637
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,200
But a stewardess can't be too chubby.

638
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:02,840
Of course.

639
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,160
The plane can't take off
if the stewardess is chubby.

640
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:07,800
Have you ever flown in a plane?

641
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,070
I...

642
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:10,830
No, I haven't.

643
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:11,950
But Hua has.

644
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,000
Have you?

645
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,560
I've flown in a plane several times.

646
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,280
I heard they serve free drinks
on the plane.

647
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,040
Did you have drinks?

648
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:22,630
Yes, she did.

649
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:24,240
She had the drinks on the plane.

650
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:24,960
So,

651
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:26,150
did you see the stewardess?

652
00:33:26,150 --> 00:33:27,000
How do they look like?

653
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:27,840
Describe them to us.

654
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:28,720
I know. I know.

655
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:30,520
I often watch them on television.

656
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:32,310
They tie a silk ribbon here,

657
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:33,800
and wear a long skirt.

658
00:33:33,820 --> 00:33:34,760
Then they will do this.

659
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,030
Dear travellers,

660
00:33:36,030 --> 00:33:36,740
now...

661
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:37,910
Travellers?

662
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:39,320
Travellers are travel by train.

663
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,480
On a plane, people are called passengers.

664
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,400
It's like this.

665
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:45,510
Welcome to CM666 fight.

666
00:33:45,510 --> 00:33:48,720
This flight will fly from Tieyuan
to Shenyang.

667
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,520
The plane lands as soon as it takes off.

668
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:52,600
She only knows one big city,
which is Shenyang.

669
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:53,950
She didn't know any other cities.

670
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:54,630
Harbin.

671
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:55,920
I know the big cities.

672
00:33:58,200 --> 00:33:59,640
Are there men working on the plane?

673
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:00,550
Of course.

674
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:02,230
The steward and captain are all male.

675
00:34:02,230 --> 00:34:03,680
Someone has to carry the luggage.

676
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,800
If it's true, Fan Shuishui can it.

677
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:07,000
You are responsible to carry the luggage.

678
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:09,199
And I am

679
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:11,000
very suitable to be the captain.

680
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:14,310
The captain on television
wears sunglasses.

681
00:34:14,670 --> 00:34:17,120
I look really good when I wear sunglasses.

682
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,480
They are always in a group

683
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:20,270
walking across the airport.

684
00:34:20,270 --> 00:34:22,000
Oh my goodness!

685
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:23,230
It was so cool.

686
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:25,310
Let's try to imitate them.

687
00:34:25,310 --> 00:34:26,679
Come on.

688
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:29,920
From now on, I am the captain.

689
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,030
You are the co-pilot.

690
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:32,860
Okay.

691
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,320
You are the luggage.

692
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:35,670
You two are the stewardesses.

693
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:36,360
Come on.

694
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:37,989
Line up.

695
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,120
Take the luggage.

696
00:34:45,909 --> 00:34:47,860
[Summer Special: Iced Drinks, Tieyuan
Popsicle and Shaved Ice with Fruits]

697
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,239
Look at you.

698
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:51,679
Can you be a pilot?

699
00:34:52,159 --> 00:34:53,520
Not a pilot.

700
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,469
They said that I am suitable
to be a steward.

701
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:58,080
Mr Wang,

702
00:34:58,350 --> 00:35:00,200
your son wants to be a steward.

703
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:03,270
Isn't it a job for girls?

704
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:05,000
Can you do something manly?

705
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,150
They are not all girls.

706
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:07,350
There are also boys.

707
00:35:07,350 --> 00:35:08,550
It's a classy job.

708
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:10,550
Just let him go if he wants to.

709
00:35:10,550 --> 00:35:12,040
He is rarely this serious
about doing things.

710
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:13,560
But,

711
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,920
I have to get trained first.

712
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,320
And I need to pay for the training.

713
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:17,320
How much is it?

714
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:19,910
One thousand yuan.

715
00:35:19,910 --> 00:35:20,790
Why is it so expensive?

716
00:35:20,790 --> 00:35:23,510
Aviation college trainings are not cheap.

717
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,120
How much do you spend on drinks?

718
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:27,560
Is it so hard to give us some money?

719
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,230
That's not what I mean.

720
00:35:30,230 --> 00:35:31,480
I was just curious.

721
00:35:34,750 --> 00:35:35,600
Thank you, Mr Wang.

722
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,600
I'm going out now.

723
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,190
Here's a piece of good news.

724
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:50,030
I have joined the training for stewardess.

725
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:52,080
I might be a stewardess someday.

726
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:53,350
Stewardess?

727
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:56,480
Everyone joined the training.

728
00:35:57,310 --> 00:35:58,750
Do you want to join us?

729
00:35:58,750 --> 00:35:59,680
It's not my cup of tea.

730
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,000
Just give it a shot.

731
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,030
By the way,

732
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:06,160
you can learn something new.

733
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:10,560
So you don't need my tutoring, right?

734
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,030
That's not what I mean.

735
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:15,080
If you don't need tutoring,

736
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:17,230
you don't need to memorise
the notes I give you too.

737
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,550
Why is he angry without any reason?

738
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:41,680
Why are you gloomy?

739
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:45,880
We have graduated.

740
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:46,800
There's nothing we fear.

741
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:48,150
We are adults now.

742
00:36:48,900 --> 00:36:50,040
Crap.

743
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,990
Nobody cares even if
you are not admitted to a university.

744
00:36:51,990 --> 00:36:53,240
But someone cares about me.

745
00:36:54,310 --> 00:36:56,120
I guess after the results is out,

746
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:57,640
my uncle will kill me.

747
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,080
What will you do then?

748
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:00,790
What can I do?

749
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,040
Just admit my mistake.

750
00:37:03,080 --> 00:37:04,040
Why don't we have a barbecue?

751
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:05,400
No.

752
00:37:05,750 --> 00:37:06,390
I'm going home.

753
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:07,710
I will be caught if it's too late.

754
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,520
Why isn't she back? It's so late now.

755
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:24,230
She's been out the whole day.

756
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:26,920
Mom, I got to pick her up.

757
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,280
You never cared for me that much!

758
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:45,840
What did you do today?

759
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:47,080
I bought books.

760
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:51,040
Your dad is in poor health recently.

761
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:53,000
Don't make him angry.

762
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:54,520
Next month,

763
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,160
we will invite Professor He over.

764
00:37:56,640 --> 00:37:58,430
He is your dad's college classmate.

765
00:37:58,430 --> 00:37:59,430
When the time comes,

766
00:37:59,430 --> 00:38:01,000
behave well, okay?

767
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:03,640
Okay.

768
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:05,880
Drink the milk.

769
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,850
[Pipi Lu Collection]

770
00:38:26,900 --> 00:38:27,680
Why are you here?

771
00:38:28,590 --> 00:38:29,670
Where is Hua?

772
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:30,600
She has gone home.

773
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:31,720
No, she hasn't.

774
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,920
I waited for a long time at home
but didn't see her.

775
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:35,120
She left for home after six o'clock.

776
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,830
Then where is she?

777
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:39,790
It's so late now.

778
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,000
She should be fine, right?

779
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:47,440
Wait, where are you going?

780
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:48,480
Let's look for her separately.

781
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:07,800
Is that Li Qing Tong?

782
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:09,160
It seems to be her.

783
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,070
Hey, girl.

784
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:55,160
Your bike broke down?

785
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:55,800
Come on.

786
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,760
Let me help you.

787
00:39:58,900 --> 00:39:59,470
No, thanks.

788
00:39:59,470 --> 00:40:00,230
No, thanks.

789
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:01,880
Don't worry.

790
00:40:02,110 --> 00:40:03,200
Let me buy you a drink.

791
00:40:03,550 --> 00:40:04,160
After that,

792
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:05,680
I will give you a new bike.

793
00:40:07,900 --> 00:40:09,400
No, thanks.
My house is back there.

794
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,840
Where are you going?

795
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:13,760
What are you doing at this hour?

796
00:40:17,900 --> 00:40:18,920
Who are you?

797
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,760
Who are you?

798
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,110
We were just talking.

799
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,230
Why did you interrupt?

800
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:24,800
I am her elder brother. What do you want?

801
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:25,640
Elder brother?

802
00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:26,800
Do you want to be beaten?

803
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,120
I won't be so sure if I were you.

804
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:30,070
No, wait.

805
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:31,680
Don't fight with them.

806
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:32,960
Let go of me.

807
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:35,440
What are you doing? There are two of us.

808
00:40:36,230 --> 00:40:37,640
Then just come over here.
